title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.3: CHILD PROTECTION MECHANISM

description.narrative: More communities have strengthened mechanisms to protect children from violence, abuse, and exploitation including FGM/C and child marriage., which contributes to Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more girls and boys are protected from violence, abuse and exploitation and benefit from improved response and prevention systems

title.narrative: More communities have strengthened mechanisms to protect children from violence, abuse, and exploitation including FGM/C and childmarriage.

description.narrative: Families, children, adolescents and youth have increased awareness, knowledge and ;skills to address and respond to gender inequality, social norms, and violence against children through awareness raising, advocacy, engagement; in programmatic interventions, community dialogue, youth forums, and Girls/ schools clubs, life skill training, and social media. 57 communities participated in public declarations of the abandonment of FGM ;as a result of Saleema social marketing, community dialogues, health and legal sessions and the media. About 29,733 adolescent girls received prevention and care interventions that helped them address child marriage. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:18/01/2022
